  "prompt": "What would happen if your visa to live and work in Dubai was about to expire, you'd paid any debts but you had no money to fly home?",
  "response": "If your visa to live and work in Dubai is about to expire and you have no money to fly home, there are several potential steps you can take:\n\n1. **Contact your consulate or embassy**: Reach out to your country's consulate or embassy in the UAE. They may offer guidance on repatriation assistance or emergency travel funds.\n\n2. **Seek assistance from friends or family**: If possible, contact friends or family members who might be able to lend or give you money for a return ticket.\n\n3. **Employer support**: Talk to your employer to see if they can provide or advance funds for your travel. Sometimes employers are willing to assist in such situations.\n\n4. **Emergency funds**: Look into local charities, non-profits, or government agencies that may provide support in emergency situations for expatriates.\n\n5. **Extend your visa**: If you are able, consider applying for a visa extension. This may give you additional time to figure out your travel arrangements.\n\n6. **Personal loans**: Consider taking out a small personal loan if you have access to such financial resources.\n\nIt's important to take action as soon as possible to avoid overstaying your visa, which can result in fines and legal complications.",
